  <fr:p>We define the states of the automaton be the Nerode congruence classes. For each letter <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \in  \Sigma ]]></fr:tex>, we add a transition between the congruence classes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[x]]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[xa]]]></fr:tex>. This is well-defined and deterministic by definition of the congruence. It is also obvious that a DFA for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}]]></fr:tex> cannot have less states.</fr:p>
